definition: a polysaccharide that is the chief constituent of all plant tissues and fibers

positive_examples: This is an example of cellulose.
We observed cellulose in this context.
A typical case of cellulose would involve these features.
The concept of cellulose applies here.
A structural polysaccharide that forms the primary component of plant cell walls and is indigestible by humans.
negative_examples: This is an example of starch, not cellulose.
The document was filed in the cabinet.
She walked to the store to buy groceries.
training_hints.disambiguation: Not to be confused with: Starch, or other types of Carbohydrate
